Male genitalia. Sternum 8 deeply emarginate medio-apically. Tergum 10 wide and subangulate to subtruncate medio-apically (
Fig. 129
), with two long subapical macrosetae and two apical setae. Sternum 9 with moderate triangular emargination apically, two long subapical macrosetae and one apical seta at each side (
Fig. 128
). Aedeagus with median lobe gradually narrowed from base of paramere; apex of median lobe acute (in dorsal view) and simple in its apical fourth (in lateral view); paramere elongate and entire, leaf-like, with apex acute, almost reaching apex of median lobe, with two lateral rows of sensory peg setae joined at apex (
Figs. 130, 131
). Internal sac with distinctly sclerotized structures (
Fig. 130
).
